WEBVTT

00:01:35.079 --> 00:01:37.159
There's a nurse at our military hospital.

00:01:37.799 --> 00:01:38.599
Tang Ju'er.

00:01:38.599 --> 00:01:39.480
Tang Ju'er.

00:01:40.480 --> 00:01:42.599
She's about the same age as this Ye Biying.

00:01:43.280 --> 00:01:45.040
She should know something.

00:01:45.799 --> 00:01:46.680
Indeed.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:50.640
You mean the daughter of that Tang Bingchen?

00:01:50.840 --> 00:01:51.200
Yes.

00:01:51.599 --> 00:01:53.040
They should know each other.

00:01:56.319 --> 00:01:56.920
Telegraph room.

00:01:56.920 --> 00:01:58.480
Send a telegram to Inoue Kamakura.

00:02:00.040 --> 00:02:03.239
Tell him to mind his own business.

00:02:04.159 --> 00:02:04.959
That colonel...

00:02:04.959 --> 00:02:07.519
...is carrying a letter in His Majesty's own handwriting.

00:02:08.319 --> 00:02:09.280
A person like that...

00:02:09.280 --> 00:02:10.560
...is best left alone.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:12.560
Do you hear me?

00:02:15.039 --> 00:02:19.479
Has my father replied?

00:02:19.479 --> 00:02:20.639
Yes.

00:02:20.759 --> 00:02:22.599
What did he say?

00:02:24.319 --> 00:02:25.879
Mr. Inoue Akira says that Imperial Investigator...

00:02:25.879 --> 00:02:28.479
...is carrying a letter in His Majesty's own handwriting.

00:02:28.479 --> 00:02:33.439
A person like that is best left alone.

00:03:10.280 --> 00:03:12.000
You can't do this.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:14.199
Are you really sanding the propeller with sandpaper?

00:03:15.360 --> 00:03:16.439
You want to try my job?

00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:19.240
I work three shifts a day.

00:03:19.240 --> 00:03:21.800
And there are hundreds of planes waiting for repair.

00:03:21.800 --> 00:03:22.439
Getting yours fixed now...

00:03:22.439 --> 00:03:23.439
...is your lucky day.

00:03:23.439 --> 00:03:24.240
Sir.

00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:24.639
Sir.

00:03:24.639 --> 00:03:25.800
We mean no offense.

00:03:25.800 --> 00:03:26.919
We've already shown you...

00:03:26.919 --> 00:03:27.759
...General Arnold's orders.

00:03:27.759 --> 00:03:30.039
These planes need to be finished ASAP.

00:03:31.960 --> 00:03:33.599
Can you please stop?

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:34.560
Don't you know...

00:03:34.560 --> 00:03:36.199
...we have to fly across the Pacific?

00:03:36.680 --> 00:03:38.280
If you keep sanding it...

00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:39.919
...salt will make the blade tips warp.

00:03:40.479 --> 00:03:41.639
The Pacific.

00:03:41.639 --> 00:03:42.919
Finally, someone tells me...

00:03:42.919 --> 00:03:44.800
...where these things are going.

00:03:45.319 --> 00:03:47.080
That's none of your business.

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:48.879
Listen.

00:03:49.759 --> 00:03:52.360
If the commander really wants to do this...

00:03:52.360 --> 00:03:54.280
...maybe I have a good method that suits you.

00:03:54.280 --> 00:03:57.199
Modify these planes.

00:03:57.520 --> 00:03:58.120
But for now...

00:03:58.120 --> 00:03:59.560
...my job is...

00:03:59.599 --> 00:04:01.960
...to do these meaningless tasks.

00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:04.400
Alright.

00:04:04.560 --> 00:04:06.120
Look at the marks you made on the propeller.

00:04:06.919 --> 00:04:08.560
Apply some lubricant and smooth it out.

00:04:09.120 --> 00:04:09.520
Thank you.

00:04:36.439 --> 00:04:37.240
Boys, wake up!

00:04:37.240 --> 00:04:38.199
We're moving out.

00:04:43.879 --> 00:04:46.800
March 28, 1942.

00:04:46.879 --> 00:04:48.879
The Doolittle Bomber Squadron...

00:04:48.879 --> 00:04:52.000
...transfers to Sacramento for training.

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:15.560
Dr. Ozutsu.

00:05:16.639 --> 00:05:17.920
Private Second Class Kainoshin...

00:05:18.959 --> 00:05:21.600
...seems worse than yesterday.

00:05:21.959 --> 00:05:23.160
Would you go check on him?

00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:26.360
Understood.

00:06:19.800 --> 00:06:21.480
Tang Ju'er.

00:06:22.519 --> 00:06:24.519
What are you doing?

00:06:32.879 --> 00:06:33.720
Let's go.

00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:36.480
We're going to the comfort station.

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:42.920
Wait, I'll take you there.

00:06:52.120 --> 00:06:54.040
I heard you've been looking for this book.

00:06:54.040 --> 00:06:56.160
I specifically asked a friend in Shanghai to find it.

00:06:56.160 --> 00:06:57.480
I brought it back, hoping you'd like it.

00:06:59.560 --> 00:07:01.480
I've been looking for this book.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:03.839
Thank you so much.

00:07:04.959 --> 00:07:06.199
Have you read this book?

00:07:06.759 --> 00:07:07.040
Yes.

00:07:07.519 --> 00:07:08.079
What do you think?

00:07:09.600 --> 00:07:11.199
This amazing American author...

00:07:11.199 --> 00:07:13.879
...when he wrote this book in 1921...

00:07:13.879 --> 00:07:16.639
...already predicted...

00:07:16.639 --> 00:07:18.560
...that Japan would launch a surprise attack...

00:07:18.560 --> 00:07:20.319
...on Pearl Harbor from the north Pacific.

00:07:20.319 --> 00:07:21.519
Admiral Isoroku Yamamoto...

00:07:21.519 --> 00:07:22.600
...when he served as a military attachÃ© in the US...

00:07:22.600 --> 00:07:25.800
I think before he made this decision...

00:07:25.800 --> 00:07:27.759
...he must have read this book.

00:07:28.839 --> 00:07:29.639
Colonel.

00:07:30.439 --> 00:07:31.879
I'm convinced.

00:07:33.480 --> 00:07:34.600
You are a man of talent by the Emperor's side.

00:07:34.720 --> 00:07:35.519
You've always been able to grasp...

00:07:35.519 --> 00:07:37.480
...the pulse of those admirals' decisions.

00:07:38.959 --> 00:07:41.399
I only have people find books for me after the fact.

00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:42.839
That's why I'm only a lieutenant general out here.

00:07:43.199 --> 00:07:44.839
I'm just a colonel right now.

00:07:45.120 --> 00:07:45.920
No, no, no.

00:07:46.079 --> 00:07:47.839
You will become a general.

00:07:48.680 --> 00:07:49.519
You flatter me.

00:07:50.079 --> 00:07:51.000
By the way.

00:07:51.199 --> 00:07:52.079
Your Excellency, Commander.

00:07:52.279 --> 00:07:53.879
There's one more thing I'd like to ask of you.

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:55.439
What is it?

00:07:57.160 --> 00:07:58.279
This time, under orders...

00:07:58.279 --> 00:08:00.360
...to investigate Admiral Osumi Mineo's crash...

00:08:00.839 --> 00:08:01.759
...I need a unit on the island...

00:08:01.759 --> 00:08:03.319
...to assist me.

00:08:04.079 --> 00:08:05.160
The Special Police Brigade...

00:08:05.160 --> 00:08:06.240
...has very close ties...

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:07.279
...with the Shanghai garrison.

00:08:07.360 --> 00:08:09.319
So they can't be fully trusted.

00:08:09.879 --> 00:08:12.560
Admiral Osumi Mineo was always in the Navy.

00:08:12.560 --> 00:08:13.560
So I hope you...

00:08:13.680 --> 00:08:15.879
...can draw a unit from the Navy...

00:08:15.879 --> 00:08:17.600
...to assist my work.

00:08:17.800 --> 00:08:19.439
The officer's rank need not be too high.

00:08:19.920 --> 00:08:20.800
But preferably, this unit...

00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:22.160
...should avoid having members of the Southern Expansion Faction...

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:24.199
...or the Northern Expansion Faction.

00:08:25.120 --> 00:08:25.759
Colonel.

00:08:26.680 --> 00:08:27.759
Don't take those guys from the Special Police Brigade...

00:08:27.759 --> 00:08:28.920
...seriously.

00:08:29.439 --> 00:08:31.000
They're just a bunch of guard dogs.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:32.320
They'll bark at anyone who comes in.

00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:34.919
In my Marine Corps...

00:08:34.919 --> 00:08:36.519
...there's an anti-aircraft battery.

00:08:36.840 --> 00:08:37.879
Their main task is...

00:08:37.879 --> 00:08:39.480
...to guard the port and airfield.

00:08:40.360 --> 00:08:42.279
The Chinese army has no air superiority.

00:08:42.279 --> 00:08:43.360
They haven't had much to do.

00:08:44.360 --> 00:08:45.799
Apart from leaving personnel on combat-ready duty...

00:08:45.799 --> 00:08:46.279
...you can deploy this unit anytime.

00:08:46.279 --> 00:08:46.960
You can deploy this unit anytime.

00:08:48.159 --> 00:08:48.840
Excellent.

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:51.240
Then tomorrow, I'll establish my investigation headquarters...

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:52.879
...at the anti-aircraft battery.

00:08:54.240 --> 00:08:56.519
Let Adjutant Sakamoto arrange your rest first.

00:08:56.519 --> 00:08:57.279
Tomorrow...

00:08:57.279 --> 00:08:58.200
...I'll notify all department heads to hold a welcome banquet...

00:08:58.200 --> 00:09:00.279
...for you at the headquarters.

00:09:00.799 --> 00:09:02.399
The commander of the anti-aircraft battery...

00:09:02.399 --> 00:09:03.159
...is First Lieutenant Akinokawa Ken.

00:09:03.159 --> 00:09:04.320
I'll have him come meet you.

00:09:04.480 --> 00:09:05.320
Thank you.

00:09:22.039 --> 00:09:22.919
Ozaki

00:09:24.879 --> 00:09:25.399
Is the examination finished?

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:26.799
Not yet.

00:09:27.519 --> 00:09:28.240
Come here.

00:09:28.240 --> 00:09:29.039
I need to talk to you.

00:09:30.519 --> 00:09:31.159
Hurry up.

00:09:34.759 --> 00:09:35.799
Bring the medical kit.

00:09:59.399 --> 00:10:01.240
Who did this?

00:10:09.960 --> 00:10:10.399
Come here.

00:10:11.279 --> 00:10:12.000
Examine her.

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:12.919
Yes.

00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:30.080
You didn't use any improper methods, did you?

00:10:31.799 --> 00:10:32.879
I can swear.

00:10:32.879 --> 00:10:34.240
Absolutely not.

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:36.840
Then why did Ye Degong refuse?

00:10:40.799 --> 00:10:41.440
Sir.

00:10:42.960 --> 00:10:43.840
If I may be so bold.

00:10:44.840 --> 00:10:46.720
Aren't we being too polite with these people?

00:10:50.080 --> 00:10:51.559
Are you questioning me?

00:10:53.080 --> 00:10:54.000
I wouldn't dare.

00:10:55.759 --> 00:10:57.200
Let me tell you again.

00:10:58.320 --> 00:11:00.159
The key to rule lies in mind and spirit.

00:11:01.559 --> 00:11:03.440
Not physical torture.

00:11:04.480 --> 00:11:06.279
Ye Degong is the clan leader of this island.

00:11:06.879 --> 00:11:08.360
Conquer him,

00:11:08.519 --> 00:11:09.840
and you conquer all of Sanzao Island.

00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:11.720
Understood.

00:11:18.200 --> 00:11:21.720
What do you think of the Colonel who just arrived?

00:11:25.399 --> 00:11:26.120
Well...

00:11:28.200 --> 00:11:31.799
What I've been fearing has finally happened.

00:11:33.039 --> 00:11:34.440
General, you mean...

00:11:36.840 --> 00:11:38.240
The incident last year involving Admiral Osumi Mineo's plane crash.

00:11:38.240 --> 00:11:39.440
It caused a huge uproar.

00:11:40.480 --> 00:11:41.360
It alarmed His Majesty.

00:11:41.360 --> 00:11:42.840
Because Prime Minister Konoe Fumimaro stepped down,

00:11:44.399 --> 00:11:46.639
the investigation was shelved for a time.

00:11:47.159 --> 00:11:49.279
I never thought it would be reopened now.

00:11:50.720 --> 00:11:51.600
Could it be...

00:11:52.720 --> 00:11:55.240
the Colonel is here for this matter?

00:11:56.440 --> 00:11:57.399
He not only wants to clarify

00:11:58.320 --> 00:12:00.320
the true cause of Admiral Osumi's accident,

00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:01.360
but also to find

00:12:02.159 --> 00:12:04.360
the confidential documents lost in the crash,

00:12:04.360 --> 00:12:05.360
which only His Majesty,

00:12:05.360 --> 00:12:06.399
the Prime Minister, and military chiefs possess.

00:12:07.759 --> 00:12:08.600
Is the General worried this matter

00:12:09.679 --> 00:12:10.360
might implicate

00:12:10.360 --> 00:12:12.279
officers from our 6th Air Base?

00:12:15.120 --> 00:12:15.720
You know as well as I do,

00:12:15.720 --> 00:12:17.279
the Navy and Army are constantly feuding.

00:12:19.320 --> 00:12:20.559
Admiral Osumi

00:12:20.559 --> 00:12:22.320
had already narrowly escaped several assassinations.

00:12:23.639 --> 00:12:24.879
Why this time

00:12:24.879 --> 00:12:26.120
did it have to happen in my jurisdiction?

00:12:27.600 --> 00:12:28.159
Sir,

00:12:28.919 --> 00:12:30.679
don't worry too much.

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:33.279
It might just be an accident.

00:12:34.039 --> 00:12:35.279
Unrelated to us.

00:12:37.639 --> 00:12:38.919
We can't rule out that those

00:12:38.919 --> 00:12:40.639
hot-headed radicals under our command did it.

00:12:41.480 --> 00:12:43.320
If the Colonel finds out it's connected to us,

00:12:43.320 --> 00:12:44.559
and the blame falls,

00:12:46.080 --> 00:12:47.679
I'll become the target of all criticism.

00:12:48.159 --> 00:12:49.200
Our 6th Air Base

00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:50.360
won't know peace again either.

00:12:55.159 --> 00:12:58.279
While we assist the Colonel's investigation,

00:12:58.919 --> 00:13:00.960
we must also gather necessary intelligence.

00:13:02.039 --> 00:13:03.519
During his time on this island,

00:13:04.120 --> 00:13:06.039
we must be doubly careful.

00:13:07.200 --> 00:13:07.519
Yes.

00:13:16.399 --> 00:13:17.679
This is where the doctor sits.

00:13:18.600 --> 00:13:19.240
You sit.

00:13:25.519 --> 00:13:25.840
You sit.

00:13:31.240 --> 00:13:31.879
Hold on tight.

00:13:35.879 --> 00:13:36.600
Hold on!

00:13:58.440 --> 00:13:59.159
Biying.

00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:01.679
Biying.

00:14:03.720 --> 00:14:04.039
Ye...

00:14:06.519 --> 00:14:07.000
Hello.

00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:08.360
My name is Takeki Ichiro.

00:14:08.519 --> 00:14:10.120
Pleased to meet you.

00:14:10.799 --> 00:14:12.399
I've come to bring Biying her luggage.

00:14:13.399 --> 00:14:13.919
Well then,

00:14:14.679 --> 00:14:15.720
please come in.

00:14:30.399 --> 00:14:31.120
Yingying.

00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:34.120
What are you doing here?

00:14:34.120 --> 00:14:35.159
I'm bringing your luggage back.

00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:36.360
I just calmed my father down.

00:14:37.120 --> 00:14:38.080
Why are you causing trouble?

00:14:38.080 --> 00:14:38.879
Who is it?

00:14:40.600 --> 00:14:41.080
Master.

00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:41.960
You have to come with me.

00:14:42.399 --> 00:14:43.159
Hurry, go.

00:14:43.159 --> 00:14:43.480
Go, go.

00:14:46.799 --> 00:14:47.440
Mr. Ye.

00:14:50.720 --> 00:14:51.320
What are you doing here?

00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:54.159
I'm returning Biying's luggage.

00:14:54.879 --> 00:14:55.399
Put it there.

00:14:56.200 --> 00:14:56.600
Go back.

00:14:57.399 --> 00:14:57.919
Mr. Ye,

00:14:59.600 --> 00:15:00.799
I apologize for alarming you today.

00:15:01.639 --> 00:15:02.039
I'm sorry.

00:15:02.720 --> 00:15:04.720
Your country's soldiers always act this way.

00:15:05.159 --> 00:15:06.679
Completely disregarding justice and morality.

00:15:07.240 --> 00:15:07.759
Crude.

00:15:08.519 --> 00:15:08.960
Reckless.

00:15:09.200 --> 00:15:10.240
Mr. Ye is right.

00:15:11.039 --> 00:15:12.200
Some soldiers do act

00:15:12.200 --> 00:15:13.480
in a crude and reckless manner.

00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:15.200
I am also very angry about it.

00:15:16.519 --> 00:15:17.519
I heard that you, Mr. Ye,

00:15:17.519 --> 00:15:18.919
previously served as a consul to America.

00:15:19.720 --> 00:15:21.399
You must be well-versed in diplomatic affairs

00:15:21.759 --> 00:15:22.799
and erudite.

00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:24.799
I hope to have the chance to learn from you.

00:15:27.720 --> 00:15:28.200
Auntie Four.

00:15:28.960 --> 00:15:29.399
See the guest out.

00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:30.840
Mr. Ye.

00:15:30.840 --> 00:15:32.080
I don't want to know who you are.

00:15:33.240 --> 00:15:34.559
Our family wants nothing to do

00:15:34.559 --> 00:15:35.799
with a Japanese man in uniform.

00:15:35.879 --> 00:15:36.840
Nothing at all.

00:15:37.360 --> 00:15:38.559
Stop pestering my daughter.

00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:39.639
Go back.

00:15:40.559 --> 00:15:41.279
But I need to take

00:15:41.279 --> 00:15:42.080
Ye Biying out to take care of something.

00:15:42.200 --> 00:15:42.759
Go back.

00:15:43.159 --> 00:15:43.639
Takeki Ichiro.

00:15:44.200 --> 00:15:44.720
Hurry up and go.

00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:45.720
I'm not leaving.

00:15:49.679 --> 00:15:50.159
Father.

00:15:50.879 --> 00:15:51.360
How about this.

00:15:51.879 --> 00:15:52.679
I'll see him out.

00:15:52.960 --> 00:15:53.759
I'll be back soon.

00:15:54.320 --> 00:15:54.720
Let's go.

00:15:55.440 --> 00:15:55.919
Ying'er.

00:15:57.600 --> 00:15:58.000
Father.

00:15:58.159 --> 00:15:59.000
I'll be back very soon.

00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:00.039
Rest well.

00:16:01.840 --> 00:16:02.320
Ying'er.

00:16:05.559 --> 00:16:06.639
Are you trying to get me killed?

00:16:26.480 --> 00:16:27.120
Nurse Tang.

00:17:03.480 --> 00:17:04.319
What's wrong?

00:17:04.440 --> 00:17:05.359
You're all flustered.

00:17:06.519 --> 00:17:07.880
N-no, nothing.

00:17:09.160 --> 00:17:10.240
Did something happen at the hospital?

00:17:16.480 --> 00:17:20.039
I went to the comfort station for a routine check today.

00:17:21.359 --> 00:17:23.000
I saw Huihui.

00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:24.559
Dad.

00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:26.119
Can't you think of a way?

00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:27.799
Maybe we could...

00:17:27.960 --> 00:17:28.759
...rescue Huihui.

00:17:28.759 --> 00:17:29.279
You...

00:17:29.599 --> 00:17:30.160
Stop right there.

00:17:30.799 --> 00:17:32.039
Don't even think about it.

00:17:32.319 --> 00:17:33.920
You didn't see how miserable she was.

00:17:34.839 --> 00:17:35.480
Ju'er.

00:17:36.119 --> 00:17:37.599
We can't get involved in this.

00:17:37.880 --> 00:17:39.240
And you can't handle it either.

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:42.480
If you ask me,

00:17:42.920 --> 00:17:44.920
it's her dad and her brother's fault.

00:17:45.519 --> 00:17:46.960
Why did they have to...

00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:48.519
...attack Japanese soldiers for no reason?

00:17:48.759 --> 00:17:49.960
Whose world is this?

00:17:49.960 --> 00:17:51.240
It's the Japanese world.

00:17:51.599 --> 00:17:52.720
If the Japanese don't punish her,

00:17:52.720 --> 00:17:53.440
who will they punish?

00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:56.880
Ju'er.

00:17:57.839 --> 00:17:59.920
Your dad works for the Japanese now.

00:18:00.279 --> 00:18:01.240
Why?

00:18:01.440 --> 00:18:02.640
Isn't it for our family...

00:18:02.640 --> 00:18:04.319
...to live safely...

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:07.200
...and securely?

00:18:08.119 --> 00:18:10.359
You should understand your father's good intentions.

